WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.060 --> 00:00:08.600
At the beginning of every term we invite new students and their parents

00:00:08.620 --> 00:00:13.260
for a comprehensive new student orientation where they can tour the facilities

00:00:13.400 --> 00:00:19.140
and attend various presentations to help prepare them for the year

00:00:21.380 --> 00:00:26.500
New students and parents begin by checking in couple of days before the orientation starts.

00:00:26.680 --> 00:00:30.900
It's a busy time of the year. It's time to mingle meet other - especially the volunteers

00:00:30.900 --> 00:00:36.520
and to also meet the boarding staff will help direct you over the next couple of days

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:44.500
Depending on when you arrive you will have a couple of days to relax and unpack

00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:46.300
Take a tour of the facility

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:53.780
Meet staff and student volunteers that will guide you on a tour of Bodwell or help direct you where to go

00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:09.800
There are lots of signs around the school to help you as well we have coffee we have snacks available

00:01:12.420 --> 00:01:16.480
As orientation begins it's an extremely busy time for new students and their parents

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:22.429
However, it is all done in a relaxed atmosphere and we accommodate and appreciate that everybody is new.

00:01:22.580 --> 00:01:26.960
So we're here to offer help the students to adjust

00:01:28.580 --> 00:01:37.400
When orientation begins students and parents will have to follow different schedules during this time, it's a very busy schedule for students

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:41.700
They have to meet the principals and admin

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:45.160
they have to do a placement test

00:01:46.220 --> 00:01:53.940
They will attend the citizenship presentation where they'll be exposed to various leadership activities around school

00:01:54.240 --> 00:01:57.000
They'll be fitted for their uniform

00:01:57.180 --> 00:02:04.520
They will attend a laptop distribution session and you'll be briefed about how to use their new laptops.

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:08.180
They'll attend presentation on safety

00:02:08.300 --> 00:02:12.400
They will also attend a presentation about Block E

00:02:12.460 --> 00:02:18.620
and extracurricular activities and various athletic teams around school. They will do a neighborhood walk

00:02:18.620 --> 00:02:21.900
So they're familiar with the school and its surroundings

00:02:21.900 --> 00:02:28.520
They will attend a group orientation with their counselors followed by one-on-one for their course selection

00:02:31.780 --> 00:02:36.960
They will also attend boarding life and house orientations

00:02:40.300 --> 00:02:47.880
We also help our students with opening a bank account by inviting one of the local banks to come to Bodwell

00:02:49.440 --> 00:02:56.400
Parents will have their own separate schedule. They to get to meet the principals and the admin team

00:02:56.400 --> 00:03:00.580
They attend a presentation about boarding and homestay programs

00:03:00.840 --> 00:03:06.140
They tour the City of North Vancouver Vancouver and West Vancouver

00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:15.280
They attend orientation with counselors and they can request one-on-one meeting with their counselors

00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:20.600
they get a chance to network with other parents and with school administrators and

00:03:20.940 --> 00:03:26.400
They also attend a presentation about graduation requirements and post-secondary discussion

00:03:26.700 --> 00:03:34.420
There are many activities parents and students do together - a briefing by the police department

00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:41.340
Start of the term assembly and most mealtimes are spent together

00:03:41.580 --> 00:03:45.620
During orientation is a lot to take in but be assured

00:03:45.970 --> 00:03:51.809
there is lots of time to say goodbye to your child meet the staff who will take care of your child and

00:03:51.960 --> 00:03:56.060
Meet other parents and families who are also new to the Bodwell community

